    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>26th May 5624</date>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">If there are no<lb/> “Occident traces” in the printed off<lb/>
                matter, we will not say anything<lb/> more of the few errors the Biography<lb/>
                contained. But please look,<lb/> and <hi rend="underline">let me know</hi>
                whether<lb/> the Occident head lines have<lb/> indeed been retained. I need not<lb/>
                ask you to be careful to remove<lb/> the traces in succeeding portions.<lb/> If 130
                have been printed off<lb/> they will be enough.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">As I am writing<lb/> hurriedly, I cannot stop to<lb/> recollect
                where <add>לענים</add> occurs</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>in the copy, nor did I know<lb/> that I omitted a letter in
                shilling's<add>?</add>.<lb/> But nothing is more probable.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am sorry you took the<lb/> trouble to look up the queried<lb/>
                word in the last copy in a Spanish<lb/> dictionary. The word being<lb/> Portuguese,
                you would not<lb/> likely find it among Cathi<add>?</add><lb/>
                <del>generally</del> gentry who are<lb/> proverbially exclusive.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I think it would<lb/> be better for you to address<lb/> the
                    <persName>Benjamins</persName> direct—<lb/> Address <persName>Benjamin
                    Bros</persName>—<lb/>
                <placeName>Manchester</placeName>. If you like<lb/> however, as I correspond</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>with them I will address them<lb/> for you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">How is it we get the <sic>occident</sic> here in the middle of
                the<lb/> month? I would like to get it<lb/> early so that if there are errors<lb/>
                in the Biography they may be<lb/> altered before going to press for<lb/> the
                pamphlet.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">For the present farewell</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I remain yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
